text: Olkhovka () is a rural locality (a khutor) in Otradinsky Selsoviet, Kuyurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 16 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 6 km from Yermolayevo, 10 km from Staraya Otrada. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kuyurgazinsky District
title: Olkhovka, Kuyurgazinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
